Program: Last Word
Title: Norman St John-Stevas, Lynn D Compton, Leonard Rosoman, Robert Sherman
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01cwwll
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 11 Mar 2012
John Wilson on: Politician, academic and dandy Norman St John Stevas, remembered by Michael Heseltine and Andrew Neil. D-Day hero Buck Compton - member of the Band Of Brothers company who later led the prosecution of Bobby Kennedy's killer Sirhan Sirhan. Leonard Rosoman, the war artist who documented the London blitz and taught David Hockney at art school. And Disney film songwriter Robert Sherman, who helped create the soundtrack to childhood. Show less